# Performance & Scalability Patterns for EMHASS

## Critical Rules

- **Solver Performance Monitoring**: ALWAYS track and log solver execution time, iteration count, and memory usage - set performance baselines for optimization
- **Memory-Efficient Data Structures**: Use appropriate data structures for time series - prefer NumPy arrays over Python lists for large datasets
- **Forecast Data Caching**: Implement multi-layer caching (memory + disk) with TTL expiration - cache weather forecasts, price forecasts, and ML model predictions
- **Lazy Loading Patterns**: Load optimization components only when needed - don't initialize all subsystems for simple optimization scenarios
- **Constraint Preprocessing**: Pre-process and validate constraints before solver execution - eliminate redundant or conflicting constraints
- **Asynchronous Design**: Design data retrieval and device control to be async-compatible - don't block optimization cycles
- **Resource Limits**: Implement configurable resource limits for optimization (max solve time, memory usage) with graceful degradation
- **Model Complexity Management**: Scale optimization model complexity based on available resources and time constraints
- **Data Compression**: Use efficient serialization (pickle, msgpack) for state persistence and model caching
- **Performance Profiling**: Include performance profiling hooks for identifying bottlenecks in production systems

